### Description
JavaScript function to randomly shuffle elements in an array.

### Parameters
- `array` (Array): The array to shuffle.

### Returns
- Array: The shuffled array.

### Behavior
This function shuffles the elements of the input array in place and returns the shuffled array. It uses the Fisher-Yates algorithm to ensure each permutation is equally likely.

### Edge Cases
- If the input array is empty, it will return an empty array.
- If the input array contains only one element, it will return the same array since there's only one way to shuffle a single element.",
            "code": "function shuffle(array) {
    var currentIndex = array.length, temporaryValue, randomIndex;
    while (0 !== currentIndex) {
        randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * currentIndex);
        currentIndex -= 1;
        temporaryValue = array[currentIndex];
        array[currentIndex] = array[randomIndex];
        array[randomIndex] = temporaryValue;
    }
    return array;
